==English==
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{finance}} Collective [[investment]] (such as a [[company]] or [[syndicate]]) where the investors have little or no idea what is being done.
#: 1985: ''A Manhattan-based lawyer who is an expert in "blind pool" stock issues--those with a prospectus that says we don't know what we'll do with your money--notes that one of the better tactics is pinpointing specific groups for the sales pitch.'' &mdash; [[w:Forbes|Forbes]] magazine 05.20.85 [http://www.forbes.com/free_forbes/1985/0520/038_2.html]
===Usage note===
May be used as a [[pejorative]] for a company providing poor information to [[shareholder]]s.

